text:
Haven Avenue and about 176th Street, looking west from Riverside Drive.

P. L. Sperr

Summer 1923

Haven Avenue, south from West 176th Street, showing several new apartments under construction. The far two, including the frame residence were removed subsequently and their sites are now a part of J. Hood Wright Park. At the right is W. 177th Street, continuing its winding way downhill to Riverside Drive.

May 18, 1924

Standard Photographic Service
Gift of Borough President of Manhattan
